4.5/5  rDev +2.3%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Poured from a 12oz bottle into a tulip:
Appearance: intensely dark brown, bordering on black but not as deathly oily as some imperial stouts. Still, very obsidian color.
Aroma: layer upon layer of the typical stout scents.....espresso roast, chocolate, amongst other rich, decadent layers. Really appetizing and dessert-y smelling.
Taste: terrific notes of coffee, which is easily the dominant flavor here. Not much sweetness, but the beer isn't "hot" like some higher percentage brews. The focus is coffee, and the beer delivers in that regard...tons of roastiness and complexity, with a nice bitter finish. Not nearly as sweet as the predominant flavors in imp. stouts that are popular today, but delicious and extremely well-balanced.
Feel: thick and smooth, but not sticky. Really grew into a delicious, decadent experience as it warmed. Heavy body with only mild carbonation.
Overall: an incredible stout, one of the best non-BA stouts available. Wish it was more readily available in New England. 1,007 charactersTheElectricOne, Oct 22, 2015
