4.28/5  rDev -2.7%look: 4.25 | smell: 4.25 | taste: 4.25 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.25Poured from a 12 oz bottle into a snifter.
L: Nice, mocha, lacy head. Doesn't hang long in any meaningful way, but lingers around the edge.
S: My girlfriend and I both detected chiles, like it was a Mexican stout, at first. But that's not an adjunct used, it seems. Definitely some kind of spice. Coffee is there too, obviously.
T: Roasty, roasty, roasty. Bitter coffee finish. Tastes less like brewed coffee, more like coffee beans before the brew with all that bitterness intact. All the bitterness of the beer tastes like it's from the coffee rather than the hops.
F: That bouncy, liquid metal feel that I look for in an American style stout. 
O: Very good. Not hugely memorable, but very good. 702 charactersMichaelNeelsen, Oct 19, 2015
