4.81/5  rDev +9.3%look: 4 | smell: 4.75 | taste: 5 | feel: 4.75 |  overall: 4.75Picked this up at La Capsule Cave à Bière in Nancy, France.  Thick pitch black pour with one finger caramel-colored head with decent retention and lacing.  Huge roasted coffee notes dominate the nose along with hints of dark chocolate, cocoa, vanilla, espresso, and booze.  The taste follows suit with earthy dark chocolate and coffee dominating along with hints of espresso, cocoa, chocolate fudge, vanilla, brown bread, and leather.  The mouthfeel is thick and chewy, maybe even slightly oily, with incredible balance and drinkability, and a velvety smooth finish.  Overall, this just became my favorite Coffee Stout!  Incredibly flavorful and unbelievably drinkable.  Highly recommended!!! 694 charactersbeerdrifter, May 23, 2015
