4.57/5  rDev +3.9%look: 4 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.75 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Served from a 341ml bottle to a pint glass.
A: hahaha - yep espresso! Exceptional mocha notes and quite sweat! Head disappeared super quick but who cares!
S: ABV is not evident due to dominant up front aroma of espresso and bold choc/vanilla backing. Is it a smoothie or a beer?
T: Start is certainly like 'Choc Hops' Stout from Mildura brewery with dominant choc/vanilla sweetness. Mild coffee backs it up to provide mid-palate body (I drink double espresso, so maybe stronger coffee than I state) The main theme for me appears to be the chocolate but goes deeper and longer than that through to a very solid coffee / vanilla end. 
M: Not too thick that the 'new to stout' drinker would be intimidated but certainly a hearty consistency that makes you feel as if you have got what you wanted! Well balanced bitterness and carbonation is almost spot on! 
O: Probably one of the first examples I would reach for to give to a mate who wants to experience the wonderful world of stout! The misses likes chocolate? Give her a taste! Your mate likes coffee? Nudge this fellow his way! Fantastic beer with plenty of aroma, mouthfeel and taste with big ABV that is not at all evident! 1,182 charactersladofmanor, Jun 21, 2013
