T- Flavor is much more roasty and bitter than the aroma lets on.  Pronounced booze presence as well.  Notes of dark chocolate, espresso and char.  
M- Slightly creamy with medium-low carbonation and a full body.
O- A big, bold coffee stout that has sweetness in the nose but a full-on black coffee flavor.  Good  stuff but it leans too much toward the burnt roastiness for me.  I like my coffee beers a bit more smooth and balanced.  That's what keeps me from giving it a higher score. 856 charactersImmortale25, Dec 03, 2012
