4.22/5  rDev -4.1%look: 4 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4.5Fairly fresh bottle poured into Duvel tulip right out of the cellar (~55deg.).
A: Very deep brown, bordering on pure black. Head is a rather large and fluffy mocha, which hangs around for a while after some initial settling. Very delicious looking stout.
S: Tons of fresh roasted coffee beans, dark chocolate and that nice imperial stout toasted malt. Minimal sweetness despite the chocolate. My wife says it smells "molasses-ey"
T: Excellent roasted coffee flavors overpower. Very true to a great cup, the coffee is neither bitter or week and watery, with tons of smooth roasty complexity that keeps you coming back. Beyond the coffee is some dark cocoa and a hint of bittering hops.
M: Nice balance, not too thin or viscous. Creamy without being lactic, coats the tongue and hangs around for quite a while. A fair amount of bitterness, reminiscent of dark chocolate.
Overall, this holds up to the hype. It reminds me of an "imperial" version of Surly Coffee Bender, which is a good thing. I am really glad this is available relatively easily in my area, as it is one of the best coffee beers I have had. 1,107 charactersdoucmehu, Jan 08, 2012
