Texas Liquor
Carlsbad, CA
Black on black with an inch-high brown head. Leaves a mess of stick down the glass. Perfect!
Incredibly luscious aroma consisting of coffee, coffee, and coffee, along with lots of pleasant roast, and some sweet and earthy vanilla notes. As the beer warms, a lovely bittersweet chocolate note presents itself. This is incredible!
Earthy vanilla, lots of coffee, tons of roasted malt, and a moderate level of bitterness. I swear this also had a bourbon barrel character as well, but I don't know much about this beer--is it barrel aged? This is a complete, delicious coffee stout. There's no hint of alcohol whatsoever. I'm so glad I finally cracked this one--it's tremendously delicious!
Medium to thick mouthfeel and oh so drinkable!
Perhaps the best, always-available coffee imperial stout on the market (it certainly ranks with Speedway!). This is tremendous beer! Exceptional. 918 charactersehammond1, Oct 25, 2011
