The flavor is very good, with tons of rich, earthy coffee. Fantastically bitter as well. However, these are the only two notes I'm getting, and two notes don't make a complex chord for my taste buds, at least when I'm drinking an imperial. Mouthfeel is good; very creamy but not as luscious as some big, bad stouts. 
This is an excellent beer, and I'm definitely a coffee guy-- grind them whole beans and brew a mean pot to get me going almost every morning. Yet, when I drink an imperial stout I don't really want to be drinking coffee, coffee, COFFEE. Maybe I'll have Peche Mortel for breakfast sometime. 897 charactersdasenebler, Jan 13, 2010
4.62/5  rDev +5%look: 4 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 5 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4.5Alright, time to see just how good the #1 Canadian beer is.
Appearance: Unsurprisingly black as night, and produced a deep brown finger of head the stuck around for a long time, but did not really lace all the much.
Smell: An espresso smell is putting it mildly as rich waves of coffee aroma are coming off of this wit with hints of vanilla and light chocolate. Very nice scent and potency, but I would have also liked a bit of malt.
Taste: Wow, this is a very well balanced beer as it seems to come in waves of well balanced coffee nuances. Starts with a bit of malt and turns to a balanced chocolate. However every part of this beer brings rich coffee beans to the table. I want to give it a 4.75 as some more beer elements could be present. However, given it is clearly labeled a coffee beer, I'm willing to let it slide.
Mouthfeel: Beautiful transitioning, excellent carbonation however probably it's weakest quality is the very bitter, almost earthy aftertaste that is a bit too pungent. However it does not linger which is a plus.
Drinkability: The only thing that stops this beer from going down is the aftertaste, and the fact there are times, when you simply don't feel like having coffee. Smooth going down and a strong coffee presence that will wake you up. 
Final Thoughts: Well played BDC, well played. I do not think I will experience a coffee beer that is quite this good again. This beer is so good, I'm pretty sure I won't be able to drink another Mill St Coffee Porter ever again. It's deserving of it's spot as the #1 Canadian beer that is for certain. 1,577 charactersTheHammer, Jan 13, 2010
