4.87/5  rDev +10.7%look: 4.5 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 4.5A- Pours smoothly, resulting in a very dark, opaque brown body, with minimal visible carbonation, and a creamy light-brown head. Wonderful lacing and decent head retention for a 9.5% beer.
S- Mostly espresso beans, with nice hints of dark chocolate, and very roasty, almost tobacco-like undertones. Very impressive!
T- First, it kicks in with a powerful roasted coffee bean flavour, then follows into a sweet, chocolate-like and slightly bitter taste. Finally, the finish consists of lingering roastiness (again, almost tobacco-like). One can also taste some hops, but it may be quite a challenge with all of the powerful roasted coffee flavours. As you approach the end of the glass, the alcohol starts becoming more defined, but, still, it does not get in the way, as you will still fully enjoy this stout (if you're into stouts and coffee).
M- Very smooth. Medium-bodied, a bit like molasses. The alcohol content in the taste is disguised quite well, too, even though you do get a warm feeling from it. This stout coats your whole mouth, producing a wonderful sensation and a feeling of joy.
D- Moderation is key with this one. Although it drinks quite smooth, I would recommend against having more than one at once. 1,223 charactersNightINgale, May 18, 2009
