4.2/5  rDev -4.5%look: 4.5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4Appearance: Massive tan head, looks like it's gonna be a while for it to go down. Body is a pitch black. For 9% the lacing is intense.
Smell: An odor that just flys from the glass, loaded with chocolate, any earthy aroma, and... oh yeah, COFFEE. The smell is very pungant. The coffee is deep roasted which compliments the bitter chocolate well.
Taste: Strong. In terms of complexity, there isn't a whole lot. The few flavors that hit your tongue, however, really lay a smack down. What surprised me the most was the coffee, and not as much coffee as what I expected. Thats not to say its not there, oh its there. A bittersweet chocolate rounded out with dark somewhat tart fruit. The coffee sits in the background, filling the mouth at various spots. 
Mouthfeel: Carbonation level is low, a very slick stout which compliments the lasting taste very well.
Drinkability: At 9% the alcohol doesn't overwhelm you, but it'll creep up on you. A very intense flavour, maybe 2 of these, if I could find another one. 1,011 charactersjslot38, May 13, 2008
4.33/5  rDev -1.6%look: 5 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 3.5 |  overall: 4Thanks markgugs for this one.
Small capped bottle poured into a snifter. Bottled 10/07.
It is pitch black, with a voluminous tan head, quite fluffy and extensive, as big as I have seen for high ABV beers. It slowly drops down to a collar that lasts forever, leaving a lot of sticky, extensive lacing on the sides of the glass. It cannot look better than this. 
Aroma is, as expected, coffee and more coffee. There is, however, some roasted malts and chocolate under, and not being a coffee drinker myself I cannot really express it very well, but this coffee just smeels better than others; perhaps it is a bit more delicate, not overpowering yet still easy to smell. 
Medium to full bodied, perhaps its only significant flaw is lacking a bit more body; taste is just as the aroma suggested; coffee, but not overpowering and for some reason, better than other coffee stouts for someone that is not a coffee drinker; now what does that mean to a coffee drinker, I do not know - this coffee, to me, just tastes better. 
One small bottle is more than enough, but this is one coffee stout, to me a style in itself that I would get a few more if I had the chance. Well made indeed. 1,177 charactersbrdc, May 11, 2008
