4.41/5  rDev +0.2%look: 5 | smell: 4 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.511.5 ounce bottle poured into my Dogfish Head snifter
A - This is about as nice as they come. Pitch black with about a one inch foamy tan head head. Head dissapates slowly, leaving a layer of foam. Plenty of lacing on the glass.
S - Coffee up front with some roasted malt in the background.
T - Starts with some roasted malts and dark chocolate flavors and then moves to bitter coffee. The bitterness from the coffee and bitterness from the hops blend perfectly together and linger on the tongue for a while. As the beer warms up, some dark fruit flavors become present.
M - Thick and creamy. Carbonation is a little heavy at first.
D - This is almost too drinkable. I would never guess this to be close to %10 ABV. It's scary how drinkable this is.
I'd have to say this is the best coffee stout I've had, but if you're not a fan of coffee I could see you not liking it. To those who like coffee, this is a treat. 919 charactersmoose3285, May 09, 2008
