Pours jet black with a good sized tan head, head is very similar to a cola at first by fading fast, slows down though and leaves some patchy lacing.
Smell has a strong presence of coffee, coffee, and a little bit of coffee, roasted malt in there as well.
Taste starts out with a carbonation kick which seems out of place, almost like a cola, after the onslaught of bubbles in the mouth is when the coffee taste kicks into gear and the beer becomes more creamy and thick. Not the creamiest stout I've had, as a result of the high carbonation, but it is rather viscous nevertheless. The strength is also well hidden, only a slight alcohol presence near the end, but it might also be the bitterness of the coffee, hard to tell.
