4.97/5  rDev +13%look: 4.5 | smell: 5 | taste: 5 | feel: 5 |  overall: 5Received this brew from DarkerTheBetter recently in a trade. I absolutely love coffee Stouts and this is the best of the best, can't wait! Drank from my Black Butte Porter pint glass.
Appearance- Pours midnight black with a nice one finger dark tan head. A cap and collar remains until the very bitter end of the beer and even then a huge collar remains. A bit of lacing is left reminding me of the sweet nectar that once was.
Smell- Thank the lord! I was worried this would be one of those "themed" stouts that wouldn't be dominated by the theme. Loads of roasted coffee beans are abundant in this one. Starbucks would be proud! A bit of bittersweet chocolate and some sweet caramel is noticeable.
Taste- Very roasted with plenty of dark bitter baker's chocolate before the coffee makes its presence known. Very bitter and powerful the coffee is the absolute focal point of this beer. Dark and roasted with a sweet caramel undertone before a bit of alcohol crashes the party. Finishes with a long French roasted coffee aftertaste that lingers on for days. Absolutely fantastic!
Mouthfeel- Medium to full body with a smooth creamy feel and medium sharp carbonation. A bit of warming after the swallow but nothing overly harsh.
Drinkability- After first taste, I really enjoyed this beer thought it had possibilities; after the second, I'm almost 100% sure this is the best beer I've ever tried (to date). The only complaint that I have with this brew is that it's a bit warm toward the end but a little bit of time will cure that nicely. Although if I had to choose between keeping the intensity of the coffee and or loosing a bit of warming, I'd definitely keep the coffee. Great beer that I thoroughly enjoyed (wish it was American), big thanks to Ed! 1,754 charactersyounger35, Apr 11, 2008
