A-Like most Imperial Stouts, it pours a deep dark black with hints of brown on the very edges when held up to the light. A very nice one finger medium brown head of dense foam appears, but doesn't disappear completely, instead settling to a 1/16" that stays while I drink... nice!
S-A nice casual coffee, roasted malt smell greets me. Not overly intense, but pleasant.
T-The coffee is the main feature here.... a nice roasted coffee, roasted grains taste. Chocolate, cocoa, almond and even a mild hint of licorice also appear. Some hops are hiding in the background but for the most part are an afterthought. I wavered on a higher rating for taste, but there is a very very faint metallic taste that's noticeable nonetheless...
M-When warmed up, the mouthfeel is sublime. Creamy, smooth, well carbonated (yet not overly so) and the thickness is spot on for this style.
D-Of course, the ABV would limit you to a couple, but it's highly drinkable, pleasant to drink, and worth searching out. 
