4.41/5  rDev +0.2%look: 5 | smell: 4 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4.5 |  overall: 4.5Had a friend who went to Montreal pick this up at Rahman's for me along with some anniversary Unibroue. As a coffee geek, I'm super excited to review this! Cellar temp. Dated 11/07. 9.50% abv, 341mL bottle. Poured into an oversized wine glass.
Stunning crema of a head (espresso reference), bits of lace all over the glass. Body that is like a black hole. No light at all penetrates this. Best looking beer I've ever seen.
Aromas of raisin, cardboard, dark, dark chocolate, nice caramel maltiness. Brandy cherries. Coffee is extremely well integrated. I get a nice roasty note from it but there is no 'coffeeness' in the aroma. 
Mouthfeel is big and chewy, with nice carbonation. Coats the teeth. Palate is... wow. Definitely very alcoholic with a bit of sweetness but explosively rich bitterness. Raisins are back. More chocolate. Coffee comes out here, finish explodes with the fresh brewed bitterness of an espresso ristretto in a dram of Ardbeg. Big smoky roasted character. Mouth drying. Extreme. 
My first review ever was Mill Street Coffee Porter. Suffice to say this blows it away.
