4.32/5  rDev -1.8%look: 4 | smell: 4.5 | taste: 4.5 | feel: 4 |  overall: 4Received bottle via trade many moons ago.
Appearance: Pours a thick opaque black into a goblet style glass. Mocha colour head disappears rather quickly to a lacey ring with a small island floating in the centre. 
Aroma: Intense roasts coming out of this one. Espresso aroma absolutely dominates, however it is rich, roasty & intense, not like some of those other "coffee" beers that come across more as camp coffee flavour added to a porter. Alcohol is definately present as it whaffs up in between layers of espresso, dark roasted malts and burnt caramel.
Taste: More intense espresso flavours here. The initial blast is dry, astringent and very roasty, but the espresso comes through huge in the finish with a flavour that lingers endlessly. The bitter coffee flavour is sort of a love hate relationship similar to hoppy IPA's, you just can't help but drinking more.
Mouthfeel: If I searched for flaws, it is here. Could use a little more body to support the 9.5% abv, but it is certainly good as is. Carbonation is soft. Drinkability is high for it's style.
Final Statement: A remarkable achievement in beer. The perfect coffee beer. Highly recommend. 1,159 charactersMMansfield, Mar 25, 2008
